2. What information we collect

We collect and process the following categories of information. Some items below are collected directly by the App; others may be collected by third‑party services that we use (for example, ad networks or analytics providers).

A. Information you provide directly
- Support requests: If you contact us (email or in‑app support), we may collect your email address and any other information you provide in the message in order to respond.

B. Automatically collected information
- Device information: model, operating system version, device identifiers (subject to platform rules), language, and device capabilities.
- Usage and gameplay data: gameplay events (levels played, scores, achievements, time spent), preferences, and non‑personal statistics used to improve gameplay and UX.
- Crash and performance data: crash logs and diagnostics to detect and repair bugs and improve stability.
- Advertising identifier: the mobile advertising identifier (Advertising ID on Android / IDFA on iOS) may be accessed by ad SDKs to serve personalized and non‑personalized ads.

C. Local storage
- The App uses local storage (for example SharedPreferences on Android) to keep game progress, preferences (sound, haptic), and lightweight settings.

D. Payment / purchases
- If the App offers in‑app purchases, purchase receipts or transaction identifiers may be processed by the underlying app store (Google Play, Apple App Store). We do not directly process payment card numbers.

E. Third parties
- Third‑party services used by the App (such as ad networks, analytics, crash reporting, or cloud services) may collect, store, and process information. These services operate under their own privacy policies. We list common examples below but you must confirm which providers you use in your build and update this policy accordingly.

Common third‑party types used in mobile games:
- Advertising networks (e.g., Google AdMob)
- Analytics and crash reporting (e.g., Firebase Analytics / Crashlytics)
- Platform services (Google Play Services)

3. How we use the information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
- To operate and provide the App and its features (game state, progression, loading levels).
- To personalize the user experience (game suggestions, in‑game content, ad preferences if applicable).
- To serve and optimize ads, including using advertising identifiers to support personalized or non‑personalized advertising.
- To diagnose and fix technical issues, crashes, and abuses.
- To measure and analyze usage so we can improve the App.
- To prevent fraud and abuse.
- To respond to your support requests.

4. Legal basis for processing (EU / EEA)

If you are in the European Economic Area (EEA) or the UK, our legal bases for processing personal data are:
- Performance of a contract (providing the App and game features).
- Legitimate interests (improving and securing the App, serving ads—where interests are not overridden by your rights).
- Consent: where required by law (for certain cookies, tracking, or targeted advertising) we will ask for consent prior to processing.

